title: Rachael Sanna
text: Rachael Sanna (née Downs) (born 17 December 1972 in Sydney, New South Wales) is an Australian <a href="Equestrianism">equestrian</a>. She competed at the <a href="2000%20Summer%20Olympics">Sydney 2000 Olympics</a> in the <a href="Equestrian%20at%20the%202000%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Individual%20dressage">individual</a> and the <a href="Equestrian%20at%20the%202000%20Summer%20Olympics%20%E2%80%93%20Team%20dressage">team</a> dressage events. Riding Aphrodite, she finished in 33rd place in the individual event, while the Australian team of <a href="Kristy%20Oatley">Kristy Oatley-Nist</a>, <a href="Ricky%20MacMillan">Ricky MacMillan</a>, <a href="Mary%20Hanna">Mary Hanna</a> and Sanna finished 6th in the team event. She is married to fellow Australian equestrian <a href="George%20Sanna">George Sanna</a>.
